    <h1>Welcome to a Heroku app built for Ruby/Rack using Sinatra</br>
	        called Equation of Time.</br>
        The formula : &Delta;t = (&Mu; - &nu;) + (&lambda; - &alpha;)</br>
		  <h2>Delta = (Mu - nu) + (lambda - alpha)</h2>
    </h1>
    <p><h3>
    &nbsp&nbsp;&nbsp&nbsp;The Equation of Time is used to correct time for Solar to Clock at most locations</br>
    except those closer to the North and South poles.</p>
    <p>
    &nbsp&nbsp;&nbsp&nbsp;To convert your longitude to time, divide it by 15.0 and you will have your longitude hour.</br>
    12:00 noon UTC plus your longitude hour West of UTC or minus for East of UTC is your Mean Solar Transit Time.</br>
    Example: 12 + 75 / 15.0 = 17 hours </br>
    </br>
    &nbsp&nbsp;&nbsp&nbsp;The Equation of Time is then subtracted from your mean solar time to give you the actual clock time of Solar Transit.</br>
    Example : 17:54 - (-00:12) = 18:06</br>
    The result will be your True Solar Transit at UTC.</br>
    Just convert the time for your time zone by adding your zone offset. - 4 West, + 5.5 East</br>
    A shadow of a stake would point North or South at this time depending on your location from the Equator.
    </p>
